---
By: Shantidasa
Locus:
  Page: 263
  Verse: 3
Tags:
  - Elusions
---
Being ignorant of his true identity, man has evolved to be his own worst
enemy. Observing his outside surroundings, man often perceives it as an
illusionary foe. A fierce struggle inevitably ensues and the end may be
predicted with absolute certaintyï¼š man loses, wounding himself in the
process.
